==English==

===Alternative forms===
* [[vermillion]] (considered a misspelling by some authorities)

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fr|en}} {{term|vermeil||vermilion|lang=fr}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|lang=la|vermiculus||little worm}}, from {{term|lang=la|vermis||worm}}, ultimately in reference to {{taxlink|Kermes vermilio|species|noshow=1}}, a type of scale insect used to make a crimson dye.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/vɜː(ɹ)ˈmɪl.jən/|lang=en}}
* {{rhymes|ɪljən|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[vivid]] [[red]] [[synthetic]] [[pigment]] made of [[mercury sulfide]].
# A vivid red or slightly [[orange]] [[colour]].
#: {{color panel|E34234}}
{{quote-Fanny Hill|part=3
|I, struggling faintly, could not help feeling what I could not grasp, a column of the whitest ivory, beautifully streak'd with blue veins, and carrying, fully uncapt, a head of the liveliest '''vermilion'''}}
# A type of red dye worn in the parting of the hair by married Hindu women.
# A red skin of the lip or its border with the skin of the face.

